I didnt see a response, so I thought I would chime in.

How about the voltage regulator (if one exists on a '63)??  I had a similar
situation on my daughter's pl*mouth a while back, and I replaced both my '67
bus before everything was happy.  I dont remember the circumstances on the
bus, but what you described was identical to my daughter's car.

Voltage regulators are pretty cheap ($15 or so at the neighborhood FLAPS);
and is worth a shot.

--Rich


