Here, I'll throw an emergency question out to all you experts.

I put my new engine in the '63 Sundial. When I fired it up the alternator
will start to charge (13 on the Vmeter), but when I roll out of the garage
the VDO volt meter goes only very slightly to the charge and if I turn on
the lights it goes strong to the discharge, and the Gen light glows dully.

I have put in all new wires in the engine compartment and to the starter. I
have replaced the Bosch New Man alternator with a new one with no change.

Help! Help!

